'''Mini-Rigs''' was a sub-set of [[Kenner Products|Kenner's]] [[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (toy line)|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] and [[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (toy line)|''Return of the Jedi'']] toy lines. The small toy vehicles were offered at a lower price point than standard vehicles due to their small size. Besides the Mini-Rigs, Kenner also released three [[Body-Rigs]].<ref name="Offscreen" />

The toys, initially designed by [[Mark Boudreaux]], were meant to be vehicles "just out of sight" in the movies. Some made later appearances in the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]].<ref name="Offscreen" /> ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' refers to the [[PDT-8 Personnel Deployment Transport]] as a "[[mini rig]]", though the term was not applied to any other of those vehicles in fiction.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|III|15|PDT-8}}</ref>

